# Smart Lighting Market by Lights and Luminaire, Lighting Controls, LED Drivers and Ballasts, Sensors, Switches, Gateways, Dimmers, Relay Units, DALI, Power Over Ethernet (PoE), Power Line Communications (PLC) and Zigbee - Global Forecast to 2030
## Description
The global smart lighting market was valued at USD 9.86 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 17.38 billion by 2030; it is expected to register a CAGR of 12.0% during the forecast period.

## Market Drivers
The increasing adoption of LED lighting and luminaires in outdoor applications, growing penetration of data analytics in smart lighting, emerging smart offices and smart retail trends, rising adoption of human-centric lighting, and development of solar-powered and hybrid smart lighting solutions are the major drivers contributing to the market growth.

## Market Restraints
Cybersecurity concerns associated with internet-connected lighting systems and difficulties associated with retrofitting traditional lighting infrastructure are the major restraints for the market growth.

## Market Opportunities
Development of solar-powered and hybrid smart lighting solutions, emerging smart office and smart retail trends, rising adoption of human-centric lighting, growing adoption of PoE-based lighting solutions in commercial and healthcare applications, and increasing demand for personalized lighting control solutions are the major opportunities for the market growth.

## Market Challenges
High upfront costs of equipment and accessories and interoperability and compatibility issues are the major challenges for the market growth.

## Outdoor Application Segment
The outdoor application segment is expected to grow at the highest CAGR during the forecast period due to increased investments in urban safety initiatives, smart city infrastructure, and mass-level public lighting deployments that are energy-efficient.

## Offline Distribution Channel Segment
The offline distribution channel segment is expected to lead the market during the forecast period as smart lighting consumers continue to use physical channels as their preferred choice for purchase.

## India
India is expected to have the highest CAGR in the Asia Pacific smart lighting market owing to fast urbanization, government policies supporting energy efficiency, and smart city projects on a large scale.

## Breakdown of Primaries
The study contains insights from various industry experts, ranging from component suppliers to Tier 1 companies and OEMs. The break-up of the primaries is as follows:
- By Company Type: Tier 1 - 55%, Tier 2 - 25%, Tier 3 - 20%
- By Designation: Directors - 50%, Managers - 30%, Others - 20%
- By Region: North America - 40%, Europe - 35%, Asia Pacific - 20%, RoW - 05%

## Competitive Landscape
The smart lighting market is dominated by a few globally established players such as Signify Holding (Netherlands), Acuity Brands, Inc. (US), Panasonic Holdings Corporation (Japan), Legrand (France), Zumtobel Group (Austria), and ams-OSRAM AG (Austria), among others.

## Research Coverage
The report segments the smart lighting market and forecasts its size by offering, installation type, end-use application, distribution channel, communication technology, and region. The report also discusses the drivers, restraints, opportunities, and challenges pertaining to the market.

